## New-Paradigm: Provenance Upgrade PR

This PR upgrades the repository to the New-Paradigm living-repo standard.

### Summary
- Adds automated provenance artifact production (.provenance/PROVENANCE.signed.json)
- Adds provenance-check workflow to block merges missing provenance
- Declares ARCHITECTURE_MANIFEST.json, META_LAYER_RULES.md, SYSTEM_BOUNDARY_CONSTRAINTS.json
- Adds verification & audit utilities

### Rationale
This upgrade enforces reproducibility, provenance, and prevents stealth copying or unnoticed architecture modification. It preserves the existing code and training logic while adding transparency and an auditable trail.

### Reviewer checklist
- [ ] Confirm `ARCHITECTURE_MANIFEST.json` reflects intended system
- [ ] Confirm `META_LAYER_RULES.md` access policy matches maintainers' intent
- [ ] Confirm `SYSTEM_BOUNDARY_CONSTRAINTS.json` paths are accurate
- [ ] Confirm workflows use required secrets (PROV_API_TOKEN) only where appropriate
- [ ] Merge requires 2 approvals from maintainers

### How to test locally
1. Run `.github/scripts/verify_provenance.py .provenance/PROVENANCE.signed.json` (create a dummy PROVENANCE if needed)
2. Run sample metrics extraction: `python3 create_visualizations.py` (project-specific)
3. Run audit compare: `python3 audit/report_audit.py before.json after.json`
